    "name": "Juan Heredia (4)",
    "profile": "Juan Heredia is a percussionist of the Spanish band [a=cHAMBAo] since 2004. He was born in Tangier, Morocco, but moved to Málaga, Andalusia, Spain as a young child. He comes from a family of artists, mostly percussionists. In 2008, he was nominated for a Latin Grammy for Chambao's album \"Con Otro Aire\". He has a long and distinguished musical career, having performed alongside artists such as [a=Pastora Soler], [a=El Chino], Bambino, [a=Carles Benavent], [a=Javier Ruibal], Antonio Manzanita, [a=Remedios Amaya], [a=Tomatito], Parrita, [a=Ricky Martin], [a=Bebe (4)], [a=Antonio Carmona], [a=Pasión Vega], among many others.",
